McGUIRE v. ANLETA et al. (Common Pleas of New York City and County, General Term. May 16, 1894.) Action by Mary A. McGuire, as executrix, against Agnesa Anleta and others.

Argued before BOOKSTAVER, BISCHOFF, and PRYOR, JJ.

T. J. McKee, for plaintiff. F. J. Moissen, for defendants.

No opinion. Taxation affirmed. The cases referred to are not applicable to an action for partition.
